    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">The kernel trick is a functor in disguise: it maps from a data category to a feature-space category, preserving inner-product structure. The SVM optimization problem is convex, so gradient descent finds the global minimum. Support vectors are the critical points that pin the decision boundary.</p>

